<span id="freeTextContainer2777635729901022895">I got this book for Christmas that year. This was my first ever Anne Rice book, and it was about a year after Interview With A Vampire came out as a movie with Brad Pitt, Christian Slater and Tom Cruise. I was blown away people. If you like a story, like <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18405.Gone_With_The_Wind' title='Gone With The Wind by Margaret Mitchell' rel='nofollow noopener'>Gone With the Wind</a> on crack, no seriously, epic like that, except VERY ADULT (don&apos;t let your tweens get their hands on this one Mom&apos;s and Dad&apos;s!), but such an addicting read that you may just get fired for calling in sick over it.<br/><br/>This was far an</span>
  <span id="freeText2777635729901022895" style="display:none">I got this book for Christmas that year. This was my first ever Anne Rice book, and it was about a year after Interview With A Vampire came out as a movie with Brad Pitt, Christian Slater and Tom Cruise. I was blown away people. If you like a story, like <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18405.Gone_With_The_Wind" title="Gone With The Wind by Margaret Mitchell" rel="nofollow noopener">Gone With the Wind</a> on crack, no seriously, epic like that, except VERY ADULT (don't let your tweens get their hands on this one Mom's and Dad's!), but such an addicting read that you may just get fired for calling in sick over it.<br /><br />This was far and away my favorite Anne Rice novel, and any of the other sequels and prequels that go with it, and a major recommendation from me on great, compelling, lose-yourself type reading.</span>
