<span id="freeTextContainer5845804640108617752"> Engrossing from the first paragraph. Anne Rice is best known for her book, &quot;Interview With the Vampire,&quot; but she SHOULD be best known for this. <br/> This is an epic novel that follows the lives of the Mayfair witches through generations, time and place. Eerie, magical, and mysterious. Characters are woven into an intricate and mesmerizing plot. Beautiful descriptive writing. <br/> I was chilled to the bone and genuinely scared during nearly every chapter, but addicted like nothing else. Stayed up way pa</span>
  <span id="freeText5845804640108617752" style="display:none"> Engrossing from the first paragraph. Anne Rice is best known for her book, "Interview With the Vampire," but she SHOULD be best known for this. <br /> This is an epic novel that follows the lives of the Mayfair witches through generations, time and place. Eerie, magical, and mysterious. Characters are woven into an intricate and mesmerizing plot. Beautiful descriptive writing. <br /> I was chilled to the bone and genuinely scared during nearly every chapter, but addicted like nothing else. Stayed up way past my bedtime with this one. Or was it because I was too scared to go to sleep? ;)</span>
